            "description": "One-loop massive Bhabha scattering family with 5 master integrals (tadpole $T_1$, two bubbles $T_2(t)$ and $T_3(s)$, one vertex $T_4(t)$, one box $T_5(s,t)$). Massive electron line, massless photon exchange. Canonical UT basis $g_1..g_5$ constructed via Magnus exponential of the $\\varepsilon^0$ part of the DE matrix; the resulting canonical system $d g = \\varepsilon d \\hat{A}_1 g$ is logarithmic in Landau variables $x,y$ defined by $s=-m^2(1-x)^2/x$ and $t=-m^2(1-y)^2/y$, with seven letters $\\{x,1+x,y,1+y,1-y,x+y,1+xy\\}$. Same MIs are reused as one-loop x one-loop subtopologies of the two-loop QED vertex family. Cross-checked against Henn-Smirnov 1307.4083.",
