            "description": "One-loop box integral family contributing to Bhabha scattering in $d=4-2\\varepsilon$ dimensions. Two massive propagators ($D_1, D_3$ with electron mass $m$) and two massless propagators ($D_2, D_4$). All four external legs on-shell at $p_i^2=m^2$. Used to illustrate the logarithmic restriction algorithm: the small-mass expansion $m\\to 0$ is computed as a restriction $z_1=m^2/(-s)\\to 0$. The residue matrix eigenvalues $\\{0, -\\varepsilon\\}$ split the solution into a holomorphic piece (rank 3, eigenvalue 0) with a logarithmic correction (rank 2, eigenvalue $-\\varepsilon$). Both restricted subsystems are derived and solved.",
