            "description": "One-loop box integral family for Bhabha scattering with two massive and two massless internal propagators and four equal-mass external legs. Used as a primary example to demonstrate the diagonal basis prescription for intersection numbers. On the double cut $\\{z_2, z_4\\}$, the Baikov polynomial is explicitly given and the C-matrix is computed in both the standard and diagonal prescriptions, yielding a $4\\times 4$ diagonal C-matrix. Also studied on a single cut $\\{z_1\\}$ where the massless propagators require a modification to the diagonal basis prescription.",
